All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Runnable, java.util.concurrent.Future<java.lang.Void>, java.util.concurrent.RunnableFuture<java.lang.Void>
public class GenerateTestData
extends javax.swing.SwingWorker<java.lang.Void,java.lang.Void>

This class has the job of generating test data to the artefacts and their facets. The factes have had been specified before the this process started. If no settings had made on the facets the process of generating test data would not have started.

This process may take some time in generating the data and there're a lot of I/O bound tasks involved, too. So it is separated from the EDT to the background. To give feedback, though, a status dialog is used. The dialog itself is set to the foreground and is modal, so no other task is permitted while doing the job. This is because with this approach no changes to the artefacts and facets are guaranteed.
